<subSubSection id="C32E21EAFFA8FFCC4C58FD74FB535AAF" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCC4C58FD74FDED5DEF" blockId="24.[377,528,729,754]" box="[377,528,729,754]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
(
<figureCitation id="130F6EE4FFA8FFCC4CA3FD74FE235DEF" box="[386,478,729,754]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[828,907,850,872]" captionTargetBox="[830,1438,198,807]" captionTargetId="figure-668@19.[827,1441,195,810]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. A, Marionina sp. ‘Snow Is.’ (CE34647), anterior body (lateral view). B, Marionina aestuum, sectioned specimen BMNH 1933.2.23.895, cephalic region (lateral view). C, M. aestuum (CE12477), cephalic region (ventral view). D, Marionina georgiana (paralectotype 13), cephalic region (ventral view). Abbreviations are defined under ‘Taxonomy’. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461109" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461109/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">FIGS 9A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130F6EE4FFA8FFCC4CCDFD74FDF55DEF" box="[492,520,729,754]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="24.[145,224,1817,1839]" captionTargetBox="[148,757,1616,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-808@24.[145,760,1613,1777]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 14. Marionina sp. ‘Snow Is.’ (CE34647). A, chaetal bundle. B, anterior part of body. Abbreviations are defined under ‘Taxonomy’. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461125/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">14</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCC4DB0FC8CFDAD5CCD" blockId="24.[145,761,801,976]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4DB0FC8CFE865C2B" box="[145,379,801,822]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Material examined:</emphasis>
SMNH198155 (CE34647) and SMNH198156 (CE34648), two semi-mature specimens from Snow Island (South Shetland Islands), 
<collectingCountry id="F32332F1FFA8FFCC4F5BFCF3FD085C69" box="[634,757,862,884]" name="Antarctica" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
. For information on collection localities and GenBank accession numbers for 
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4CBBFC31FE375CAC" box="[410,458,924,945]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">COI</emphasis>
barcodes, see 
<tableCitation id="C6B647DAFFA8FFCC4F51FC31FD3B5CAC" box="[624,710,924,946]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="3.[144,208,419,441]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Table 1. Specimens from the Southern Hemisphere used in this study, with specimen identification number, region of the collection site, GenBank accession numbers for the seven genetic markers, and voucher numbers (with museum acronym)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF4B22E9FFB3FFD74DB1FE0EFBE15ECA" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" tableUuid="DF4B22E9FFB3FFD74DB1FE0EFBE15ECA">Table 1</tableCitation>
and the Supporting Information (
<tableCitation id="C6B647DAFFA8FFCC4CFCFC17FDBD5CCD" box="[477,576,954,976]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="3.[144,208,419,441]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Table 1. Specimens from the Southern Hemisphere used in this study, with specimen identification number, region of the collection site, GenBank accession numbers for the seven genetic markers, and voucher numbers (with museum acronym)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF4B22E9FFB3FFD74DB1FE0EFBE15ECA" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" tableUuid="DF4B22E9FFB3FFD74DB1FE0EFBE15ECA">Table S1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCC4DB0FC57FEAC5A63" blockId="24.[145,762,1017,1560]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4DB0FC57FEDC5B12" box="[145,289,1018,1039]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Description:</emphasis>
Live colour unknown; and specimens apparently without pigmentation. Length of first 16–19 segments 
<quantity id="4CCCDF84FFA8FFCC4C4FFB9AFDF85B51" box="[366,517,1079,1100]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" unit="mm" value="2.65" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.9 mm</quantity>
(fixed, amputated specimens); first 15 segments 
<quantity id="4CCCDF84FFA8FFCC4CCAFBF8FD8C5B76" box="[491,625,1109,1131]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.3 mm</quantity>
long; width at XII 
<quantity id="4CCCDF84FFA8FFCC4DFEFBD9FEBA5B94" box="[223,327,1140,1161]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" unit="mm" value="0.27">0.27 mm</quantity>
. Chaetae slightly sigmoid (
<figureCitation id="130F6EE4FFA8FFCC4FA9FBD9FD175B94" box="[648,746,1140,1162]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="24.[145,224,1817,1839]" captionTargetBox="[148,757,1616,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-808@24.[145,760,1613,1777]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 14. Marionina sp. ‘Snow Is.’ (CE34647). A, chaetal bundle. B, anterior part of body. Abbreviations are defined under ‘Taxonomy’. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461125/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). Upper bundles dorsolateral (closer to lateral line than ventral bundles), with three to four chaetae anterior to clitellum, (three) four in postclitellar segments, at least to XIX. Ventral bundles with four chaetae throughout to XIX. The longest measured chaetae of each worm 55 µm long, ~3 µm wide. Epidermis densely covered with rows of pale gland cells. Clitellum not developed. Head pore at 0/I.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCC4D88FA25FB845ECD" blockId="24.[145,762,1017,1560]" lastBlockId="24.[809,1425,197,679]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
Coelomocytes numerous, 10–15 µm long; round, oval or spindle shaped; granulated, with distinct nucleus. Paired pharyngeal glands (
<figureCitation id="130F6EE4FFA8FFCC4F5FFA68FD135AC6" box="[638,750,1477,1499]" captionStart-0="Figure 1" captionStart-1="Figure 2" captionStart-2="Figure 3" captionStart-3="Figure 4" captionStartId-0="6.[145,225,1653,1675]" captionStartId-1="7.[161,239,1469,1491]" captionStartId-2="9.[163,246,967,989]" captionStartId-3="9.[829,915,1077,1099]" captionTargetBox-0="[152,1417,198,1611]" captionTargetBox-1="[170,1434,198,1426]" captionTargetBox-2="[168,774,196,926]" captionTargetBox-3="[830,1438,198,1034]" captionTargetId-0="figure-119@6.[149,1420,195,1614]" captionTargetId-1="figure-156@7.[167,1437,195,1429]" captionTargetId-2="figure-428@9.[167,775,195,927]" captionTargetId-3="figure-376@9.[827,1441,195,1037]" captionTargetPageId-0="6" captionTargetPageId-1="7" captionTargetPageId-2="9" captionTargetPageId-3="9" captionText-0="Figure 1. Majority-rule consensus tree for COI estimated with Bayesian inference. Specimens shaded in grey are from the Southern Hemisphere. Specimens in bold represent new species. Support values are posterior probabilities. Scale bar represents the estimated number of substitutions per site." captionText-1="Figure 2. Species tree estimated using the multispecies coalescent model in *BEAST. Specimens shaded in grey are from the Southern Hemisphere. Specimens in bold represent new species. Two support values are presented: first, the posterior probabilities from *BEAST; second, the posterior probabilities from the concatenated MRBAYES tree (see Supporting Information, Fig. S3), where ‘–’ indicates the absence of the node in question. Scale bar shows the expected number of changes per site scaled in accordance with the substitution rate of COI." captionText-2="Figure 3. Lumbricillus antarcticus. A, chaetal bundle (CE12480). B, anterior part of body (CE12479). C, nephridium (CE12480). D, genitalia (CE12479). E, F, spermathecae (CE12479 and CE34641). Abbreviations are defined under ‘Taxonomy’. Scale bars: 100 μm." captionText-3="Figure 4. Lumbricillus antarcticus and Marionina colpites. A–C, L. antarcticus, sectioned specimen BMNH 1933.2.23.899. A, B, spermatheca. C, genitalia. D–F, M. colpites. D, male pore and associated glands (BMNH 1933.2.23.888). E, F, spermatheca (BMNH 1933.2.23.886 and BMNH 1933.2.23.888). Abbreviations are defined under ‘Taxonomy’. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461087" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461089" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461093" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461095" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6461087/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6461089/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6461093/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6461095/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
) present in IV, V and VI; only third pair with ventral lobes and dorsally converging but connection not discernible. Origin of dorsal vessel indiscernible, but with peristomial bifurcation. Nephridia observed in 7/8–8/9, anteseptale with funnel only, postseptale elongated oval with terminal efferent duct. Brain with posterior incision, with clusters of perikarya on prostomial nerves and at ventral ends of circumoesophageal connectives (
<figureCitation id="130F6EE4FFA8FFCC49EAFED0FADD5E8F" box="[1227,1312,381,403]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[828,907,850,872]" captionTargetBox="[830,1438,198,807]" captionTargetId="figure-668@19.[827,1441,195,810]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. A, Marionina sp. ‘Snow Is.’ (CE34647), anterior body (lateral view). B, Marionina aestuum, sectioned specimen BMNH 1933.2.23.895, cephalic region (lateral view). C, M. aestuum (CE12477), cephalic region (ventral view). D, Marionina georgiana (paralectotype 13), cephalic region (ventral view). Abbreviations are defined under ‘Taxonomy’. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461109" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461109/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
). Ventral nerve cord with small subbuccal bulb (
<figureCitation id="130F6EE4FFA8FFCC49DCFE31FAAE5EAC" box="[1277,1363,412,434]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[828,907,850,872]" captionTargetBox="[830,1438,198,807]" captionTargetId="figure-668@19.[827,1441,195,810]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. A, Marionina sp. ‘Snow Is.’ (CE34647), anterior body (lateral view). B, Marionina aestuum, sectioned specimen BMNH 1933.2.23.895, cephalic region (lateral view). C, M. aestuum (CE12477), cephalic region (ventral view). D, Marionina georgiana (paralectotype 13), cephalic region (ventral view). Abbreviations are defined under ‘Taxonomy’. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461109" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461109/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
); see 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC4E08FE16FC5B5ECD" authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1890" box="[809,934,443,464]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4E08FE16FC5B5ECD" box="[809,934,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Marionina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
discussion above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCC4E60FE74FC685DBA" blockId="24.[809,1425,197,679]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Male genitalia not fully developed. Developing male cells free floating in XI. Developing sperm funnels in XI, 60–65 µm long, 40 µm wide. Thin line of cells extending backwards from sperm funnels to what will become the male opening. Developing spermathecae in V, shape uncertain. No midventral subneural glands observed.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCC4E08FD7DFB615C19" blockId="24.[809,1424,720,772]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4E08FD7DFB955DF8" box="[809,1128,720,741]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Geographical distribution:</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="3B5C783CFFA8FFCC4957FD7DFB6A5C19" location="Snow Island" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Shetland Islands">
Known only from 
<location id="8EEB24BAFFA8FFCC4871FD7DFC8C5C19" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039DC377FFA8FFCD4C13FD05FED05BD2:8EEB24BAFFA8FFCC4871FD7DFC8C5C19" name="Snow Island" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" stateProvince="Shetland Islands">Snow Island</location>
(South 
<collectingRegion id="49F0BC83FFA8FFCC4EEBFD43FB6D5C19" box="[970,1168,750,772]" country="United Kingdom" name="Shetland Islands" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Shetland Islands</collectingRegion>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCC4E08FC80FB055A33" blockId="24.[809,1425,813,1326]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4E08FC80FC655C5F" box="[809,920,813,834]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Remarks:</emphasis>
The two small specimens of this species were first believed to be juvenile 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC499FFCE1FAA45C7C" authorityName="Orsted" authorityYear="1844" box="[1214,1369,844,865]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Lumbricillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC499FFCE1FAA45C7C" box="[1214,1369,844,865]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Lumbricillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but they were placed genetically within a separate clade together with the two larger, darkly pigmented species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC4E08FC05FC4E5CA0" authorityName="Stephenson" authorityYear="1932" box="[809,947,936,957]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aestuum">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4E08FC05FC4E5CA0" box="[809,947,936,957]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">M. aestuum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC4ED1FC05FBA95CA0" box="[1008,1108,936,957]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4ED1FC05FBA95CA0" box="[1008,1108,936,957]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">M. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Upon closer examination, despite their submature condition, we found our specimens to have free-floating developing male cells, more akin to 
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4EE0FBA9FB9F5B04" box="[961,1122,1028,1049]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC4EE0FBA9FBC75B04" authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1890" box="[961,1082,1028,1049]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Marionina</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2731308FFA8FFCC4960FBA9FB9F5B04" box="[1089,1122,1028,1049]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
than to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC49E2FBA9FAAA5B04" authorityName="Orsted" authorityYear="1844" box="[1219,1367,1028,1049]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Lumbricillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC49E2FBA9FAAA5B04" box="[1219,1367,1028,1049]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Lumbricillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC4E08FB8EFC3E5B25" box="[809,963,1059,1080]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4E08FB8EFC5C5B25" box="[809,929,1059,1080]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Marionina</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
‘SnowIs.’ isclose to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC49B2FB8EFADF5B25" baseAuthorityName="Michaelsen" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1171,1314,1059,1080]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="georgiana">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC49B2FB8EFADF5B25" box="[1171,1314,1059,1080]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">M.georgiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inlacking pigmentation, having a densely glandular epidermis, about four chaetae per bundle, similar pharyngeal glands, presence of perikarya on the prostomial nerves and at ventral ends of circumoesophageal connectives, and in the presence of the subbuccal bulb. However, fully mature specimens from Snow Island and/or DNA from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC4E44FB57FC045A12" baseAuthorityName="Michaelsen" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[869,1017,1274,1295]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="georgiana">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4E44FB57FC045A12" box="[869,1017,1274,1295]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">M. georgiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be needed to establish whether the two are the same or separate species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCC4E6BFAD7FB535AAF" blockId="24.[842,1392,1402,1458]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC4E6BFAD7FB535AAF" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Christensenidrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="blocki">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4E6BFAD7FB5D5A8F" box="[842,1184,1402,1426]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">CHRISTENSENIDRILUS BLOCKI</emphasis>
DÓZSA- FARKAS &amp; CONVEY, 1998
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
