<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCD4E08F898FED05BD2" blockId="24.[809,1425,1845,1898]" lastBlockId="25.[163,779,197,1231]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="1128" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4E08F898FC655857" box="[809,920,1845,1866]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Remarks:</emphasis>
Our specimens perfectly resemble those originally described by Dózsa-Farkas &amp; Convey; therefore, we decided not to give complete descriptions and illustrations, but instead a few additional comments about the morphology. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA50F90FFA9FFCD4F0CFEAFFF135E2A" author="Schmelz RM &amp; Collado R" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" pagination="7 - 22" refId="ref25564" refString="Schmelz RM, Collado R. 2008. A type-based redescription of Pachydrilus georgianus Michaelsen, 1888, the type species of Marionina Michaelsen, 1890, with comments on Christensenidrilus Dozsa-Farkas &amp; Convey, 1998 (Enchytraeidae, &quot; Oligochaeta &quot;, Annelida). Verhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg 44: 7 - 22." type="journal article" year="2008">Schmelz &amp; Collado (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, in their comparison between 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4F45FE8CFD285E2B" box="[612,725,289,310]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Christensenidrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="blocki">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4F45FE8CFD285E2B" box="[612,725,289,310]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">Ch.blocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4D82FEEDFEC65E48" baseAuthorityName="Michaelsen" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[163,315,320,341]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="georgiana">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4D82FEEDFEC65E48" box="[163,315,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">M. georgiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, were left with a few questions that we will try to answer. First, we did not observe neuron perikarya in the prostomium of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4F0DFED0FD585E8F" box="[556,677,381,402]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Christensenidrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="blocki">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4F0DFED0FD585E8F" box="[556,677,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">Ch. blocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, similar to those described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA50F90FFA9FFCD4C8FFE31FD145EAF" author="Schmelz RM &amp; Collado R" box="[430,745,412,434]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" pagination="7 - 22" refId="ref25564" refString="Schmelz RM, Collado R. 2008. A type-based redescription of Pachydrilus georgianus Michaelsen, 1888, the type species of Marionina Michaelsen, 1890, with comments on Christensenidrilus Dozsa-Farkas &amp; Convey, 1998 (Enchytraeidae, &quot; Oligochaeta &quot;, Annelida). Verhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg 44: 7 - 22." type="journal article" year="2008">Schmelz &amp; Collado (2008)</bibRefCitation>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4D82FE16FEC65ECD" baseAuthorityName="Michaelsen" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[163,315,443,464]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="georgiana">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4D82FE16FEC65ECD" box="[163,315,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">M. georgiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and observed by us also in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4FA3FE16FCF65ECD" authorityName="Stephenson" authorityYear="1932" box="[642,779,443,464]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aestuum">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4FA3FE16FCF65ECD" box="[642,779,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">M. aestuum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4DF7FE77FF0B5EF2" box="[214,246,474,495]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">M.</emphasis>
sp. ‘Snow Is.’. Second, the dorsal blood vessel bifurcates in both species under the brain in a lumbricilline (peristomial) pattern. Third, the penial bulbs of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4C27FD98FE845D57" box="[262,377,565,586]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Christensenidrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="blocki">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4C27FD98FE845D57" box="[262,377,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">Ch. blocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, if they can be considered as such, which were described originally as compact and medium sized, were hard to distinguish, composed of a small aggregation of cells (&lt;50 µm in diameter) surrounding the superficial (non-invaginate) male pores, at least apparently similar to the penial bodies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4D9EFD43FEAB5C1E" baseAuthorityName="Michaelsen" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[191,342,750,771]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="georgiana">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4D9EFD43FEAB5C1E" box="[191,342,750,771]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">M. georgiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but lacking any prostate glands. The developing male gametes, although numerous and completely occupying segments X–XII, do not show any sign of being contained in lobed testis sacs. Based on these new elements and the presence of anucleate coelomic corpuscles in place of nucleated coelomocytes in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4DE5FC08FEC15CA7" box="[196,316,933,954]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Christensenidrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="blocki">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4DE5FC08FEC15CA7" box="[196,316,933,954]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">Ch. blocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we cannot but agree with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA50F90FFA9FFCD4FADFC08FF175CC7" author="Rota E &amp; Matamoros L &amp; Erseus C" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" pagination="417 - 436" refId="ref25417" refString="Rota E, Matamoros L, Erseus C. 2008. In search of Marionina (Clitellata, Enchytraeidae): a taxonomic history of the genus and redescription of the type species Pachydrilus georgianus Michaelsen, 1888. Italian Journal of Zoology 75: 417 - 436." type="journal article" year="2008">
Rota 
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4FEFFC0BFCF65CA7" box="[718,779,933,955]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA50F90FFA9FFCD4C3EFC69FDBD5CC7" author="Schmelz RM &amp; Collado R" box="[287,576,964,986]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" pagination="7 - 22" refId="ref25564" refString="Schmelz RM, Collado R. 2008. A type-based redescription of Pachydrilus georgianus Michaelsen, 1888, the type species of Marionina Michaelsen, 1890, with comments on Christensenidrilus Dozsa-Farkas &amp; Convey, 1998 (Enchytraeidae, &quot; Oligochaeta &quot;, Annelida). Verhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg 44: 7 - 22." type="journal article" year="2008">Schmelz &amp; Collado (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, in that 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4FBDFC69FCF65CC4" box="[668,779,964,985]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Christensenidrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="blocki">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4FBDFC69FCF65CC4" box="[668,779,964,985]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">Ch. blocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not share enough morphological characters with 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4D82FBAFFEBE5B0A" baseAuthorityName="Michaelsen" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[163,323,1026,1047]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="georgiana">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4D82FBAFFEBE5B0A" box="[163,323,1026,1047]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">M. georgiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to assume it to be closely related to 
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4D82FB8DFEBA5B28" box="[163,327,1056,1077]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4D82FB8DFEE35B28" authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1890" box="[163,286,1056,1077]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Marionina</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2731308FFA9FFCD4C07FB8DFEBA5B28" box="[294,327,1056,1077]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, which has also been supported by our molecular data. Unfortunately, we found no support for any specific placement of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4CC6FBF0FD475B6F" authorityName="Dozsa-Farkas &amp; Convey" authorityYear="1998" box="[487,698,1117,1138]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Christensenidrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA9FFCD4CC6FBF0FD475B6F" box="[487,698,1117,1138]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128">Christensenidrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA9FFCD4C3DFBD1FE3E5B8F" box="[284,451,1148,1170]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="25" pageNumber="1128" phylum="Annelida" rank="family">Enchytraeidae</taxonomicName>
as a whole, probably because of the lack of suitable outgroups with which to make comparison.
